Pre-Game Insights: Morocco has already qualified for the Round of 16, but the coach and team’s goal is to finish first in Group F.
Several predicting websites anticipate a victory for Morocco today.
Opta analyst believes that Morocco has a 60.7% chance of victory in this game, compared to 18.5% for Zambia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Atlas Lions have already secured a spot in the Round of 16 due to their high standing in Group F with four points.
Head coach Regragui spoke about the game at a pre-match press conference on Tuesday.
He acknowledged that although no game is easy, he is less worried about his player’s performance for today’s game, as it is taking place at 9 p.m. Moroccan time /8 p.m. in Cote d’Ivoire.
Others: Morocco's lineup includes Yassine Bounou, Achraf Hakimi, Yahia Attiat Allah, Nayeef Aguerd, and Sofyan Amrabat, among others.
The match, however, is a key opportunity for the Moroccan squad - who is vying to keep their leadership in the group - to finish strong with as many points as possible.
